data.description: Price improvement!! Sitting atop this sprawling 22-acre equestrian property that delivers unobstructed endless views of the beautiful South Carolina landscape is this 4 bedroom/3.5 bath Mediterranean style home.  As you enter the home you'll see the spacious dining room to your right for countless dinners to come and arches that lead you to the updated kitchen, perfect for any home chef! Directly off the kitchen is the bright airy breakfast nook that looks out onto the blank canvas fields of endless possibilities for any entertainer’s wildest dreams.  The new floor to ceiling stone gas offers a warm and inviting feel for family movie nights.  As you venture back towards the well-sized owner’s suite, you’ll notice the double French doors that open to your grandiose presidential style office or man cave.  The owner’s suite features a gas fireplace and oversized windows that allow you to view the beauty of your secluded estate and grant you access to the private patio and pergola area.  As you leave the owner’s suite and make your way up the sweeping staircase which leads you to the upper level, you will be embraced by the warm glow from the natural light provided by the oversized windows which highlight the wrought iron spindles and perfectly appointed fixtures.  As you reach the top of the staircase and glance to your left, you will notice a spacious bedroom all on its own, perfect for guests who visit and want their own private wing!  Follow the walkway overlooking both the living room and office and you’ll see a large space for entertainment.  Venture up to the movie room, equipped with speakers, all set for your fun movie nights!  Two larger-than-average bedrooms finish off the upstairs, both with a jack and jill bathroom and majestic views of the property. As you take a step back and sit out on your upstairs double balconies, you’ll find it hard to believe you’re 10 minutes to downtown Easley, 15 minutes from downtown Greenville and 30 minutes from Clemson University.  Property is fenced for horses, cows, or goats with a creek at the bottom of the property.  Don’t miss out on this opportunity to own your own-of-a-kind private piece of paradise. Agent is also owner of property.
